				\begin{document}$$ \kappa (t)=\left\{\begin{array}{c}1,\kern0.5em Before\ lockdown\\ {}\kappa, \kern0.5em During\ lockdown\end{array}\right. $$\end{document}κt=1,Before lockdownκ,During lockdown

We describe the interaction between the two subpopulations using two parameters, β12 and β21, to model the successful transmission occurring upon cross-contact between individuals of P1 and P2. The average interaction between socioeconomic groups is modeled by a 2 × 2 transmission matrix, which describes the disease transmission between and within subpopulations:
